
Chapter 4 — Pipeline Leakage
Why Deals Get Stuck

Not every lost deal is marked as Closed Lost.

Many simply... stop moving.

They stay in the same pipeline stage for weeks, sometimes months, creating the illusion of a healthy sales pipeline.

Managers see plenty of open opportunities.

Forecasts look promising.

Sales reps remain busy.

But behind the scenes, momentum has already disappeared.

This is one of the biggest sources of hidden revenue leakage.

What is Pipeline Leakage?

Pipeline Leakage occurs when a qualified opportunity loses momentum before reaching a buying decision.

The prospect hasn't said no.

But they also aren't moving toward yes.

The deal slowly becomes inactive while everyone assumes it's still alive.

